solution.implementation:
In updateActivePill() function, add:
```javascript
if (active) {
    b.style.backgroundColor = '#0f172a';
    b.style.color = '#ffffff';
    b.style.fontWeight = '600';
} else {
    b.style.backgroundColor = '';
    b.style.color = '';
    b.style.fontWeight = '';
}
```

Add to <style> section:
```css
#mini-stepper .step[aria-current="true"] {
    background-color: #0f172a !important;
    color: #ffffff !important;
    font-weight: 600 !important;
}
```

Replace current fade-in code with:
```javascript
// Wait for all layout to settle
setTimeout(() => {
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        requestAnimationFrame(() => {
            const toolbar = document.getElementById('topToolbar');
            if (toolbar) {
                toolbar.style.opacity = '1';
            }
        });
    });
}, 50);
```
Double rAF ensures layout is complete.

Start with visibility: hidden instead:
```html
<div id="topToolbar" style="visibility: hidden;">
```
Then after layout:
```javascript
toolbar.style.visibility = 'visible';
toolbar.style.opacity = '0';
requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    toolbar.style.transition = 'opacity 0.3s ease-in-out';
    toolbar.style.opacity = '1';
});
```

Don't fade in - just show immediately after layout:
```javascript
// Layout complete, show instantly
const toolbar = document.getElementById('topToolbar');
if (toolbar) {
    toolbar.style.opacity = '1';
    toolbar.style.transition = 'none';
}
```
This eliminates fade but also eliminates glitch visibility.

